title.@value: Double outlet right ventricle with non-committed ventricular septal defect

definition.@value: A congenital cardiovascular malformation that is a variant of double outlet right ventricle with concordant atrioventricular connections that is associated with ventricular septal defect that is remote from the ventricular outflow tracts and usually within the inlet or trabecular muscular septum.
